c(fg) \subseteq c(f)c(g)
f = a_0 + \dotsb + a_nx^n,
g = b_0 + \cdots + a_mx^m,
 \begin{pmatrix}  a_0 b_0 & \cdots & a_0b_m\\ \vdots & \ddots & \vdots\\ a_nb_0 & \cdots & a_nb_m \end{pmatrix} .
c(fg) = c(f) c(g)
A=k[t,u]
k
t, u
f=t+ux
g=t-ux
c(fg) = c(t^2 - u^2 x^2) = (t^2, u^2)
c(f)c(g) = (t,u)^2 = (t^2, tu, u^2)
